         <div type="translation">
            <p>To the Divine Spirits. Marcus Iulius Antistius made (this) for Iulia Rodope,
                    the best and most venerable wife.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>A Iulia Rodope is also attested in another epitaph from around the same time (EDR122010):
                    http://www.edr-edr.it/edr_programmi/res_complex_comune.php?do=book&amp;id_nr=EDR122010
                    However, the cognomen “Rodope” is not uncommon;  Solin reports another Iulia Rhodope in addition to these two. </p>
         </div>
